		<Col span="2" />
	</Row>
	</Section>
-->
	<Section id="intro" padding="top" classes="bg-neutral-900 dark:bg-neutral-900">
	<Row>
		<Col span="2" />
		<Col span="8" align="center">
			
			<!-- <h2>🌡️ SAVE AMERICA'S <strong> FORECASTS 📈</strong></h2> -->
			<!--  <p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;">Wed. May 28th 1pm ET/10am PT to Sun. June 1st 5:30pm ET/2:30pm PT on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/@wclivestream">YouTube:</a></p> -->
			<h1>Letters in response to NSF DCL</h1>

			<p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;">The US government plans to dismantle the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR). <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pT8dCoZgH_M">Watch our video</a> to learn why NCAR is the most important weather lab in the US, and read <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-026-01501-z">this article</a> for the latest about the scientists taking the US government to court over NCAR’s future.</p>

			<p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;">The Earth systems science community in the US and beyond have submitted hundreds of responses to the National Science Foundation’s <a href="https://www.nsf.gov/funding/information/dcl-nsf-intent-restructure-critical-weather-infrastructure">Dear Colleague Letter</a>, all urging the NSF to protect NCAR. The NSF has <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/13/climate/ncar-breakup-plan-nasa-noaa.html">said that these letters will not be made public</a>. This page aims to publish as many letters as we can.</p>

			<p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;">We currently have {allPosts.length} letters. If you would like to share yours, please email <a href="mailto:organizers@wclivestream.com">organizers@wclivestream.com</a> Also, see <a href="https://royalsociety.org/news/2026/02/statement-on-us-administrations-repeal-of-endangerment-finding/">the statement from the UK's Royal Society</a>, which calls on the US government to protect NCAR.</p>

			<div class= "rounded" style="background-color: #ce2c1e;">
				<p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;"><b>If you're inspired by these letters, please call your representatives and tell them to defend NCAR! You can find your representatives <a href="https://5calls.org/">on this website</a>.</b></p>
			</div>
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
			<!--

			<p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;">The Earth science community in the US and beyond have submitted hundreds of responses to the <a href="https://www.nsf.gov/funding/information/dcl-nsf-intent-restructure-critical-weather-infrastructure">NSF's Dear Colleague Letter</a> urging the NSF to protect the National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR). The NSF has <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/13/climate/ncar-breakup-plan-nasa-noaa.html">said that these letters will not be made public</a>. This page aims to publish as many as we can.</p><p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;">We currently have {allPosts.length} letters. If you would like to share yours, please email <a href="mailto:organizers@wclivestream.com">organizers@wclivestream.com</a>. Also, see <a href="https://royalsociety.org/news/2026/02/statement-on-us-administrations-repeal-of-endangerment-finding/">the statement from the UK's Royal Society</a>, which calls on the US government to protect NCAR.</p><p class="pb-0 text-lg" style="color: white;">If you're inspired by these letters, please <a href="https://5calls.org/issue/ncar-national-center-for-atmospheric-research/">call your representatives</a> and tell them to #SaveNCAR!</p> -->
			
